<title type="html"><![CDATA[Evaluating multiplayer games]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15540&amp;p=189220#p189220"><![CDATA[
Multiplayer games are a strange beast. I played them with actual fellows which is definitely a lot of fun by itself. It has some serious potential to induce a bias when it comes to notation.<br /><br />On the other side, none of the three multiplayers entries propose anything for one player. For those who played single to evaluate entries, it seems to induce the opposite bias: there is nothing funny to do in these games.<br /><br />I am interested in knowing how you evaluated these games. Having myself submited a multiplayer-only game makes this issue more personal. Note that this thread is late on purpose, to not influence notation but just understand it when it comes <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8178">RogerBidon</a> — Thu Feb 16, 2017 11:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
